The quick nav [shows the recently viewed pages|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Recently+Viewed+Pages+and+Blog+Posts]:
bq. Your last ten recently viewed pages also appear when you click in Confluence's *Search* field before you start typing a search query.

This is done by retrieving the pages via Ajax when the users click in the quick nav field. That is perfectly okay for logged-in users.
But imho it should be disabled for anonymous users, because it makes no sense for them and the Ajax call also returns a HTTP status code 401 (Unauthorized).

This is especially true for installations which use [an intermediary IIS|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFKB/Connecting+Confluence+with+IIS+7] for Single Sign-on purposes (e.g. with Kerberos), where the authenticated Windows user is not available in Confluence and therefore treated as an anonymous user. The 401 status code from the Ajax call somehow tells IIS to add a _WWW-Authenticate: Negotiate_ header to the response, which prompts a login popup in client browsers. The anonymous users can cancel that prompt without problem, but it is annoying:

!cf-recently-viewed-quick-nav-anonymous-login-prompt.png|thumbnail!

*Workaround*
Adding the following JavaScript as Custom HTML in the HEAD section:
{code:html}
<script>
(function ($) {
  if ($('meta[name="ajs-remote-user"]').attr('content') == "") {
    console.log('anonymous user detected -> disable recently viewed function in quick nav');
    RYQ.QuickNav = function() { /* nothing */ };
  }
}(AJS.$));
</script>
{code}

